      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "I'M GENEVIEVE (6) won here two back before dropping back to 1100m last time out and just having too much to do late in the race. Faithfull rides now from a much better barrier. Can sit closer with the strike jockey on board, and she can return to winning ways. SLIPPERY FISH (3) bounced back to form last start at this track and trip after a disappointing effort two starts ago. She's a lightly raced commodity on the way up and she comes here with plenty of upside. Can roll forward and give a bold sight. VIRESHA (4) missed narrowly two back before a 4.2L defeat most recently over 1100m. Back out to 1200m now is a good move and Cooper has options from the barrier. Expecting her to make her presence felt. QUEEN SELYSE (7) was too good last time out and can repeat the dose without surprising. ALOTOFBANTER (8) is next best.",
